stimulus: Among many animals, such as mice, fruit flies, and humans, each odor that an animal can smell is detected by a particular kind of sensory neuron that has a particular kind of receptor; eliminating that receptor through illness or genetic manipulation results in the inability to smell that odor. These mosquitoes were still able to find humans, suggesting that ______

answer_choices.B: like mice, fruit flies, and humans, individual mosquitoes with damage to particular receptors will be unable to detect certain odors.
answer_choices.C: researchers cannot assume that mosquitoes have the same correlation between receptors and the ability to sense certain odors that mice, fruit flies, and humans have.
answer_choices.D: researchers can assume that interfering with mosquitoes’ odor receptors is a potential way to prevent mosquitoes from feeding on humans.
